snippet.textDisplay: I will tell you how you should estimate time: You think how much time you should spend, and then the real time it willl take you is that time, times two, and then translate it to the next time unit. For example, if you think it takes two hours, then you say that it takes four days. Ten minutes? twenty hours. One day? two weeks. And so on.
snippet.textOriginal: I will tell you how you should estimate time: You think how much time you should spend, and then the real time it willl take you is that time, times two, and then translate it to the next time unit. For example, if you think it takes two hours, then you say that it takes four days. Ten minutes? twenty hours. One day? two weeks. And so on.
